# Badhuche Art Studio - Cursor AI Rules

## Project Overview
Badhuche is a premium art studio website showcasing monumental sculptures and murals. The design is inspired by award-winning architecture/art studio sites like OHArchitecture.com.au.

## Design System

### Color Palette (Warm Ivory Theme)
- Background: `#FAF7F2` (warm ivory)
- Foreground/Text: `#1A1815` (warm charcoal)
- Body Text: `#3d3835` (dark warm gray)
- Label Text: `#4a4640` (medium warm gray)
- Primary Accent: `#C2542D` (terracotta)
- Secondary Accent: `#B8963F` (antique gold)
- Muted: `#E8E4DD` (light warm gray)
- Dividers: `rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.1)`

### Typography
- Headings: `Marcellus` (serif, elegant)
- Body: `Jost` (sans-serif, modern)
- Mono/Labels: `JetBrains Mono`

### Key Design Principles
1. NO borders/outlines on cards - use shadows and subtle backgrounds
2. Sharp corners (border-radius: 0) for geometric aesthetic
3. Generous whitespace
4. Asymmetric layouts for visual interest
5. All shadows use dark charcoal tones (never white on ivory background)

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- React 19
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Framer Motion for animations
- TypeScript

## Component Architecture

### Custom Components (in /components)
- `custom-cursor.tsx` - Artistic blob cursor with particle effects
- `magnetic-button.tsx` - Buttons that react to cursor proximity
- `navigation.tsx` - Scroll-responsive nav with Commission CTA
- `project-card.tsx` - Project display with numbered overlay
- `process-section.tsx` - Interactive process timeline
- `text-reveal.tsx` - Scroll-triggered text animations
- `hero-gradient.tsx` - Animated background gradients

### Pages (in /app)
- `/` - Homepage with hero, works grid, process section
- `/studio` - About the studio and team
- `/works` - Full project portfolio
- `/contact` - Contact form and info
- `/process` - Detailed process breakdown

## Coding Standards

### Animations
- Use Framer Motion for React animations
- Prefer CSS transitions for simple hover states
- Always include `transition-all duration-300` minimum
- Use `ease-out` or custom bezier curves

### Styling
- Use Tailwind classes, avoid inline styles
- Follow mobile-first approach
- Use CSS custom properties from globals.css
- Apply `.oh-heading`, `.oh-body`, `.oh-label` utility classes

### Accessibility
- All images need alt text describing the artwork
- Interactive elements need focus states
- Maintain color contrast ratios
- Use semantic HTML elements

